# --- Rust ---
# Build artifacts. `target/` is recreated by `cargo build` from Cargo.toml.
**/target/

# Cargo.lock IS committed for binary crates (this is a binary, not a library).
# See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/guide/cargo-toml-vs-cargo-lock.html

# --- Python ---
# Bytecode caches and pyc files. Recreated on import.
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*$py.class

# Test / coverage caches.
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov/

# Virtual environments (never commit).
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/env/

# Setuptools / build artifacts.
**/*.egg-info/
**/dist/
**/build/

# --- ML artifacts ---
# Trained model weights and training data are large and regenerable.
# Run `python init.py` to recreate the random-init bootstrap, then
# `python train.py` to retrain from a self-play cycle.
**/*.pt
**/*.onnx
**/*.bin
**/*.data

# --- IDE / editor ---
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*~
**/.vs/

# --- OS junk ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
